HEADWORD: Propenyl
<hw>Pro"pe*nyl</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Propene</ets>
+ <ets>-yl</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A hypothetical
hydrocarbon radical, <chform>C3H5</chform>, isomeric with allyl and
glyceryl, and regarded as the essential residue of glycerin. Cf.
<er>Allyl</er>, and <er>Glyceryl</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

